To download project:

1) Download repository to your local machine

To install projects:

1) Open git-api folder

2) Install dependecies, using this command:

npm install or yarn install

3) Open web-app folder

2) Install dependecies, using this command:

npm install or yarn install

To run project:

1) First, run the backend. To do it, execute this command on the git-api folder (It is the folder where package.json folder is in git-api folder):

node app.js

If you have a personal access token to access to Github API, you can set it as an environment variable:

USER_TOKEN=<paste here your user token> node app.js

2)Then, run the frontend. To do it, execute this command on the web-app folder (It is the folder where package.json folder is in web-app folder):

npx next dev